When to Use Which Approach
Use Delta Sharing When:

Need a quick, reliable way to share data.
Security and compliance are critical.
Want to avoid maintaining custom solutions.
Require compatibility with multiple platforms.
Use a Custom Java Service When:

Have specific customization needs not met by Delta Sharing.
Full control over data processing is necessary.
Dealing with unique data formats or protocols.
Resources are available for development and maintenance.
Example Scenarios:

Delta Sharing Use Case: A retail company shares real-time sales data with suppliers for effective inventory management—live, secure, and efficient.
Custom Java Service Use Case: A healthcare organization shares patient data with research institutions but needs custom anonymization—specialized data handling through a custom service.